        <scopecontent>
          <p>This series primarily consists of correspondence from Dorothy
				Johnson. Folders 1-4 are a chronological series of correspondence from Dorothy
				Johnson to Kay Burnham. Folder 5 consists of undated correspondence. Folder 6
				consists of correspondence from third parties. Notable items in this series
				include Dorothy Johnson's recounting of: a story of a human skull which was
				said to have been given to the Knights Templar and used by them in ceremony;
				her interaction with Hollywood figures including Gary Cooper; her adoption by
				the Blackfoot Tribe; and the death of her mother.</p>
